Going by his steady rise in the industry, the breakthrough of fast-rising Afro Pop singer, Ajayi Solomon, otherwise known as Specdo, is not a fluke as the artiste has continued to carve a niche for himself in the industry. The singer, songwriter and entrepreneur, who dropped his fourth album in 2018 entitled: ‘Upgrade Ep,’ is currently warming up for another work, but this time in collaboration with two A-list artistes, Tekno and Solid Star, entitled: ‘Manyan.’ According to Specdo, his best is yet to come as his works, including his debut studio album entitled: ‘Community Riot’ in 2006; ‘Tatoo Baby,’ ‘Scatter Body, I Move from Grass to Grace’ really made waves. NCC to reposition Creative Industry for greatness WAP releases new new TV drama,  The Babinton Family Sean Dampte UK based singer, drops new track,‘Energy’ Mercy Johnson speaks on how she manages work and marriage According to him, “Music is my talent. I am ready to use music to help families, communities and society at large. Ace musician, 2baba, inspired me and made me join the industry. I get inspirations to write songs through personal and other people’s experiences. “Nigeria’s music industry is full of opportunities and one needs hard work to face the competition. I am open to everyone that believe in my dream. Though, I am not married, I will however need a hardworking woman who will support my career and love my job because my music is my life.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
